---

# 1. Purpose

This document defines mandatory coding standards and package organization for the AiDN Hypervisor.

The objective is to maintain a predictable, maintainable and scalable codebase.

Code consistency is considered an architectural requirement.

---

# 2. Design Principles

### CODE-1

Every package has one responsibility.

---

### CODE-2

Every package has one owner.

---

### CODE-3

Interfaces define contracts.

Implementations define behavior.

---

### CODE-4

Reading unfamiliar code should require minimal navigation.

---

# 3. Package Layout

Every service SHALL follow the same directory structure.

Example:

```text id="s0f5d7"
endpoint/

    service.go

    service_impl.go

    repository.go

    repository_pg.go

    commands.go

    results.go

    events.go

    models.go

    validation.go

    errors.go

    metrics.go

    types.go

    doc.go
```

Files SHALL be grouped by responsibility.

---

# 4. Public Surface

Each package SHOULD expose:

* one primary interface;
* public types required by that interface.

Implementation details SHALL remain unexported.

---

