---

# 6. Constructors

Every package SHALL expose one constructor.

Example:

```go id="5khgsc"
NewEndpointService(...)
```

Constructors SHALL:

* validate dependencies;
* never start goroutines;
* never perform network I/O;
* never execute database migrations.

---

# 7. Global State

Mutable global variables are prohibited.

Package-level state is prohibited.

Allowed exceptions:

* compile-time constants;
* immutable lookup tables.

---

# 8. init()

The use of `init()` is prohibited.

Initialization SHALL occur explicitly during bootstrap.

---

# 9. Logging

Every package SHALL use the shared logging interface.

Packages SHALL NOT instantiate loggers.

Every log entry SHOULD include:

* component;
* operation;
* correlation_id (when available);
* severity.

---

# 10. Error Handling

Errors SHALL use structured types.

Every error SHALL include:

* code;
* message;
* recoverable;
* optional cause.

Panic SHALL NOT be used for business logic.

---

# 11. Context

Every operation that may block SHALL receive:

```go id="ztjlwm"
context.Context
```

Contexts SHALL NOT be stored inside structs.

Contexts SHALL NOT be reused after request completion.

---

# 12. Concurrency

Every goroutine SHALL have:

* an owner;
* a cancellation path;
* a documented purpose.

Fire-and-forget goroutines are prohibited.

---

# 13. Events

Events SHALL be immutable.

Events SHALL NOT contain mutable pointers.

Events SHALL describe completed actions.

Commands and Events SHALL remain separate concepts.

---

# 14. Persistence

Repositories own persistence.

Services own business logic.

Repositories SHALL NOT contain business rules.

---

# 15. Configuration

Configuration SHALL be immutable after successful startup.

Runtime configuration changes SHALL occur through Configuration Snapshots.

Configuration files SHALL NOT be modified directly while the Hypervisor is running.

---

# 16. Testing

Every package SHALL include:

* unit tests;
* mock implementations;
* integration tests where applicable.

Public interfaces SHALL be fully testable without external services.

---

# 17. Documentation

Every exported type SHALL include GoDoc.

Every package SHALL contain `doc.go`.

Complex algorithms SHALL reference the corresponding RFC or IMP document.

---

# 18. Dependency Rules

Packages MAY depend only on:

* lower architectural layers;
* public interfaces.

Circular dependencies are prohibited.

Cross-service implementation dependencies are prohibited.

---

# 19. Code Review Checklist

Every pull request SHALL verify:

* architecture principles preserved;
* no ownership violations;
* no hidden dependencies;
* interfaces unchanged or versioned;
* tests added or updated;
* documentation updated where necessary.

---

# 20. Design Invariants

Invariant 1

One package.

One responsibility.

---

Invariant 2

Interfaces are stable.

Implementations evolve.

---

Invariant 3

Explicit dependencies only.

---

Invariant 4

Bootstrap owns initialization.

Packages own behavior.

---

Invariant 5

Predictability is preferred over cleverness.
